        "briefDescription": "The scheme “Chief Minister’s Free Cancer Chemotherapy Scheme” was launched by the Department of Health & Family Welfare, Government of Arunachal Pradesh on 1st August 2017 to tackle the growing incidences of cancer in the state.",
        "detailedDescription": [
          {
            "type": "align_justify",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "The scheme “Chief Minister’s Free Cancer Chemotherapy Scheme” was launched by the Department of Health & Family Welfare, Government of Arunachal Pradesh on 1st of August 2017 to tackle the growing incidences of cancer in the state. Under this scheme, cancer patients will be provided the commonly used medicines for the treatment of the disease free of cost with a ceiling of ₹10.00 lakh per person per year."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Objective:",
